      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_principal_treatment_centre__children_teenagers_and_young_adults_">Principal Treatment Centre (Children Teenagers and Young Adults)</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_principal_treatment_centre__children_teenagers_and_young_adults_">Principal Treatment Centre (Children Teenagers and Young Adults)</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_principal_treatment_centre__children_teenagers_and_young_adults_">PTC</xref>) is a specialist centre where children and young people diagnosed with cancer are treated during a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_children_teenagers_and_young_adults_cancer_care_spell">Children Teenagers and Young Adults Cancer Care Spell</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_principal_treatment_centre__children_teenagers_and_young_adults_">Principal Treatment Centres (Children Teenagers and Young Adults)</xref>
 see the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_children_s_cancer_and_leukaemia_group">Children's Cancer and Leukaemia Group</xref>
 website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.cclg.org.uk/CSOIR/Principal-Treatment-Centre-and-shared-care-unit-information"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Principal Treatment Centre and shared care unit information</xref>.        </p>
